[ Together ]
♪ How come they're now ♪

04:47.328 --> 04:52.624
♪ Gonna hang you ♪

04:52.709 --> 04:56.628
♪ And how did you ♪

04:56.713 --> 05:01.967
♪ Begin ♪♪

05:03.386 --> 05:08.140
Sumpqua! Sumpqua!
All out for Sumpqua.

05:08.224 --> 05:10.142
All aboard.

05:10.226 --> 05:13.061
Here you stand, Catherine,
on the threshold of life.

05:13.146 --> 05:16.815
You have graduated from my academy
with a first-rate education.

05:16.899 --> 05:18.817
Uh-huh!

05:21.029 --> 05:22.946
Fully equipped to deal with the misery,

05:23.031 --> 05:26.450
unhappiness and stupidity on every hand.
[ Squealing ]

05:26.534 --> 05:29.328
Remember: teach as I taught you.

05:29.412 --> 05:32.622
Oh, well, that man looks clean at least.

05:32.707 --> 05:36.626
This here man is in my custody,
and I don't want nobody near him.

05:38.087 --> 05:40.547
Oh, don't look at him, Catherine.

05:47.263 --> 05:49.348
[ Man Whistles ]

05:49.432 --> 05:51.558
Oh, a man of God.

05:51.642 --> 05:55.312
Sir, would you look after this girl?
[ Conductor ] Board!

05:55.396 --> 05:57.564
All aboard!
Oh, Catherine.

05:57.648 --> 06:00.859
You were a good student,
and I know you'll be a good teacher.

06:00.943 --> 06:04.654
I have to go.
Oh, Mrs. Parker.

06:04.739 --> 06:07.783
All aboard. Good-bye, darling.
Be a good girl.

06:10.828 --> 06:13.246
[ Train Horn Toots ]

06:13.331 --> 06:15.832
[ Steam Releasing ]

06:18.252 --> 06:20.629
[ Engine Chugging ]

06:30.640 --> 06:32.391
[ Chuckles ]

06:32.475 --> 06:34.935
Miss Parker didn't introduce us.
I'm Catherine Ballou.

06:36.312 --> 06:39.439
I'm drunk as a skunk.

06:42.568 --> 06:46.363
Apologize for bein' in
this disgustin' condition.

06:46.447 --> 06:49.741
I assure you I'll not inflict myself
on you further.

06:54.205 --> 06:56.915
First time in my life I ever drank.

06:56.999 --> 07:02.587
Took the pledge at the age of eight at the
Temperance Meetin' in Gratzburg, Montana.

07:02.672 --> 07:04.589
You remember that?

07:04.674 --> 07:08.593
Ah, it was a great
outpourin' of the spirit.

07:08.678 --> 07:13.098
And I'll not inflict myself
on you any further.

07:13.182 --> 07:15.142
Thank you.

07:18.521 --> 07:20.439
Tennyson.

07:20.523 --> 07:23.608
Spins a good yarn, does he, Tennyson?

07:23.693 --> 07:27.112
He's a great poet.
Poet?

07:27.196 --> 07:29.114
May I?

07:30.616 --> 07:34.286
"I stepped out of the dark
barroom into the street,

07:34.370 --> 07:36.788
where the sun beats down unmerciful,

07:36.873 --> 07:40.667
and Bent stood, hollerin',
'Come on out, Kid Shelleen.

07:40.751 --> 07:45.714
I'm gonna blow you
clear out of Tombstone and into hell!"'

07:47.175 --> 07:49.426
Tennyson's a good poet.

07:53.055 --> 07:56.975
"Kid Shelleen and the Massacre
of Whiskey Slide."

08:01.856 --> 08:04.816
Ma'am, I apologize
for my disgustin' condition.

08:04.901 --> 08:08.904
I assure you I will not inflict myself
on you any further.

08:08.988 --> 08:11.448
I wish there was
something I could do.

08:11.532 --> 08:16.161
Oh, you're very kind,
but I got here all the help he'll need.

08:16.245 --> 08:20.957
That's very true. There are good things
in the Bible for a time like this.

08:21.042 --> 08:23.627
Oh, ain't there, though?
This berth next, young lady.

08:23.711 --> 08:26.004
If you'll just step into the aisle.

08:26.088 --> 08:28.924
Oh, excuse me, ma'am.
Sorry.

08:33.513 --> 08:37.015
I reckon I won't never see you no more.

08:37.099 --> 08:39.017
It's been a pleasure knowin' you.

08:39.101 --> 08:41.645
Good-bye.
Good-bye.

08:53.324 --> 08:55.283
Yeah?

08:56.661 --> 08:58.578
Hallelujah, brother!

08:58.663 --> 09:03.250
I am here to comfort the sinner
and return the stray lamb to the fold.

09:03.334 --> 09:06.086
Let him who's troubled-
You got a match?

09:11.968 --> 09:13.552
Go on.

09:13.636 --> 09:17.097
Yeah, yeah. Hallelujah, brother!

09:17.181 --> 09:22.060
I am here to comfort the sinner
and return the stray lamb to the fold.

09:22.144 --> 09:25.772
Let him who's troubled,
let him who's- Thanks.

09:25.856 --> 09:29.234
You're welcome.
You was, uh, sayin'?

09:29.318 --> 09:31.653
Yeah, yeah, uh-

09:31.737 --> 09:36.157
Hallelujah, brother!
I am here to comfort the sinner...

09:36.242 --> 09:38.743
and-and- and all like that.

09:38.828 --> 09:40.912
Now, just a minute, pilgrim.

09:46.794 --> 09:49.254
All right. Come on in.

09:54.260 --> 09:58.555
My poor fella, are there any particular
verses you'd like to hear?

09:58.639 --> 10:00.765
Ha!
Told ya.

10:00.850 --> 10:03.101
He's about as religious as a hog.

10:03.185 --> 10:06.771
Well, there's bound to be something
in here that could help him.

10:06.856 --> 10:10.275
Keep every Sheriff easy, move.
I mean-

10:10.359 --> 10:12.277
Hands over your head.

10:19.827 --> 10:22.454
Sure glad to see you, Uncle Jed.
Likewise.

10:22.538 --> 10:26.166
Now, keep him covered now.
Open wide. Yeah.

10:27.293 --> 10:29.169
All right, come on, now.

10:29.253 --> 10:31.838
Handcuff him to that
pipe down there. Yeah.

10:36.886 --> 10:39.971
Hit him. Hit him!

10:40.056 --> 10:42.140
Hit him!

10:42.224 --> 10:45.268
[ Groans ] Hold him!
I'll hit him.

10:45.353 --> 10:48.813
[ Groaning ]

10:48.898 --> 10:51.191
Pick up the stuff.
I'll cuff him to the pipe.

10:56.322 --> 10:58.281
Come on!

11:09.335 --> 11:11.920
Let me have one of them guns.
Didn't you take his?

11:12.004 --> 11:16.800
Didn't you? Oh, Lordy, he's gonna blast
himself free. Go ahead, jump.

11:19.929 --> 11:21.554
Jump?

11:22.890 --> 11:24.224
Jump!

11:30.815 --> 11:32.774
[ Gunshot ]

11:37.780 --> 11:40.115
What-What happened?
He freed my prisoner.

11:40.199 --> 11:43.702
Who did? That Bible thumper
that was sittin' with the girl.

11:43.786 --> 11:46.121
You mean that young lady in lower five?
Yeah, that's her.

11:46.205 --> 11:48.164
Please.

11:48.249 --> 11:51.042
- Right here.
- Hey, you in there. Hey, girl!

11:51.127 --> 11:54.003
Come on, miss. Wake up.
The sheriff wants to talk to you.

11:54.088 --> 11:55.588
Come on. Wake up. Wake up.

11:56.382 --> 11:59.509
The parson you was sittin' with,
where'd he go? Did you see him?

11:59.593 --> 12:03.847
And my prisoner. Maybe he's
in the next car. Come on.

12:05.808 --> 12:08.518
[ Breathing Heavily ]
Oh, I shouldn't have done that.

12:08.602 --> 12:11.354
Oh, sure you should, honey.

12:11.439 --> 12:13.982
No question about it
in my mind at all.

12:14.066 --> 12:16.234
It was morally wrong.

12:16.318 --> 12:20.613
But it happened so fast,
I didn't know what to think.

12:20.698 --> 12:22.907
I-I was afraid he'd hurt you.

12:22.992 --> 12:24.909
That's right. That's right.

12:24.994 --> 12:27.495
You know,
he'd a-blowed my head off.

12:27.580 --> 12:29.497
[ Sniffing ] Huh?
What are you doing?

12:29.582 --> 12:33.418
Oh, I got a catarrhal condition.

12:33.502 --> 12:36.755
Well, you're-
you're too close. Scootch back.

12:36.839 --> 12:41.426
Oh, well, don't think
I was offerin' unwelcome advances.

12:41.510 --> 12:43.762
I put women on a pedestal.
I do.

12:43.846 --> 12:45.764
Further.

12:45.848 --> 12:48.057
I'm smack up
against the side right now.

12:48.142 --> 12:49.934
It's gonna get mighty
uncomfortable.

12:50.019 --> 12:52.395
You're not gonna be
in here long enough for that.

12:52.480 --> 12:56.524
You've gotta get out of here the moment
it's safe. That's what I'm anxious to do.

12:56.609 --> 12:59.486
You think I care to stay
any longer than needed?

13:02.698 --> 13:04.866
There are still people out there.

13:04.950 --> 13:06.951
Darn!

13:07.036 --> 13:09.788
I guess I'll just
have to stay put then,

13:09.872 --> 13:12.874
even though it goes
against my very grain.

13:12.958 --> 13:15.877
You take your arm away this second!
Hmm? Oh!

13:15.961 --> 13:18.963
Listen, I am supposed
to be a schoolteacher. I'll scream.

13:19.048 --> 13:21.007
[ Gasps ]
Hey!

13:22.718 --> 13:25.929
I was only gonna see
if the coast is clear.

13:33.479 --> 13:35.605
Gents out there with shotguns.

13:35.689 --> 13:38.691
Oh, what are we gonna do?
You can't stay here.

13:38.776 --> 13:41.319
Oh, Lordy, I hate shotguns.
Don't you?

13:41.403 --> 13:44.531
I mean,
they leave such an oozy corpse.

13:44.615 --> 13:47.659
But there's one chance
in a hundred I can make it.

13:47.743 --> 13:50.245
I'm gonna take that chance
for your sake,

13:50.329 --> 13:52.247
you bein' a schoolteacher and all.

13:52.331 --> 13:54.999
No, wait!
No, no, no.

13:55.084 --> 13:58.753
I'd rather get cut down
in the prime of my young manhood...

13:58.838 --> 14:02.590
than risk compromising
a nice girl like you.

14:02.675 --> 14:04.592
Here.
Oh!

14:04.677 --> 14:10.098
If they get me, though, I want you
should have my watch and chain.

14:10.182 --> 14:12.934
Oh, this is awful!

14:14.103 --> 14:16.646
Ain't it, though?

14:16.730 --> 14:18.398
You get away!

14:18.482 --> 14:21.025
Well, I just gotta watch
what's goin' on, don't I?

14:21.110 --> 14:23.611
I'll do the watching.
You get away.

14:27.324 --> 14:29.701
I thought you were lying.

14:29.785 --> 14:31.744
You mean I wasn't?

14:33.080 --> 14:34.956
All right, let's get this one.

14:40.170 --> 14:42.130
They're searching the berths.

14:46.051 --> 14:48.386
What's your name,
so's I can vote for you next election?

14:48.470 --> 14:51.556
Catherine Ballou.
Mine's Clay Boone.

14:51.640 --> 14:53.600
Good-bye, Miss Ballou.

14:57.021 --> 14:58.980
Yahoo!

15:00.941 --> 15:03.067
♪ Cat Ballou, she lived ♪

15:03.152 --> 15:05.236
♪ In Wolf City, Wyoming ♪

15:05.321 --> 15:07.572
♪ And folks here in Wyoming ♪

15:07.656 --> 15:11.034
♪ Live high off the hog ♪

15:11.118 --> 15:14.078
♪ That brand new firm
Sears and Roebuck ♪

15:14.163 --> 15:18.416
♪ Send them their catalog ♪

15:19.668 --> 15:22.086
♪ It's an upright town ♪
Yeah.

15:22.171 --> 15:24.380
♪ With kind, wonderful people ♪
Oh?

15:24.465 --> 15:26.466
♪ Reliable people ♪
Sure.

15:26.550 --> 15:29.928
♪ Friendly as can be ♪
So they say.

15:30.012 --> 15:32.931
♪ When they say howdy
they mean it ♪ Ha!

15:33.015 --> 15:37.143
♪ Yup, they're neighborly ♪ ♪ Yup,
yup, yup, yup yup, yup, yup, yup ♪

15:37.227 --> 15:42.690
♪ If only Cat had behaved ♪
♪ These folks would befriend her ♪

15:42.775 --> 15:47.070
♪ If Cat had behaved ♪
♪ Their hearts they would lend her ♪

15:47.154 --> 15:51.115
♪ But Cat was depraved ♪
♪ To hell now they'll send her ♪

15:51.200 --> 15:54.953
♪ She could have lived
like others do ♪

15:55.037 --> 15:57.121
♪ Cat Ballou ♪

15:57.206 --> 15:59.457
♪ Wicked through and through ♪

15:59.541 --> 16:03.336
♪ They'll now be hangin' Cat Ballou ♪♪

16:11.053 --> 16:12.971
[ Cat ]
Papa, what happened?

16:13.055 --> 16:16.766
That corral used to be full of horses.
I got tired of them horses.

16:16.850 --> 16:20.603
I sold 'em all off to the army at
Fort Huckabee, and good luck to 'em.

16:20.688 --> 16:23.648
You spent as much time raising
those horses as you did raising me.

16:23.732 --> 16:25.775
[ Shouts ]

16:27.194 --> 16:29.946
And the house- you haven't
had that painted since I left!

16:30.030 --> 16:34.158
Well, I like it that way... all gray
and weathered and full of splinters.

16:34.243 --> 16:37.120
Papa- Oh, come on, honey.

16:41.250 --> 16:43.918
This here's my new bronc buster.

16:44.003 --> 16:47.672
This is my daughter, Catherine.
Shalom alechem, Jackson Two-Bears.

16:47.756 --> 16:50.842
Mr. Ballou, what's the use of
saying shalom alechem to me?

16:50.926 --> 16:54.137
I'm a full Sioux Indian.
I'm not one of the chosen people.

16:54.221 --> 16:56.806
All right, go ahead bein' stubborn
if you want. I ain't stubborn.

16:56.890 --> 16:58.808
Oh, not much you ain't.

16:58.892 --> 17:01.492
You know, according to an ex-congressman
of these United States...

17:01.562 --> 17:04.063
I heard give a lecture
at the Chautauqua this winter,

17:04.147 --> 17:06.357
Injuns is the lost tribe of Israel.

17:06.442 --> 17:08.526
But he won't admit it.
Just ain't true.

17:08.609 --> 17:11.945
He was an ex-congressman
of these United States, I tell ya.

17:12.031 --> 17:15.116
Papa, maybe he was mistaken.
Why, no, he was not.

17:15.200 --> 17:19.162
Jackson's just got a mean,
stubborn streak in him is all.

17:19.246 --> 17:22.165
I brought Mr. Bernstein,
the telegraph operator,

17:22.249 --> 17:26.210
out here from town last month, and he
stood right where you're standing now...

17:26.295 --> 17:29.630
and he talked Hebrew at Jackson
for ten minutes by my watch...

17:29.715 --> 17:32.925
and Jackson pretended
he didn't understand a word.

17:33.010 --> 17:36.804
Now, I call that stubborn! Well,
I didn't understand a word.

17:36.889 --> 17:38.931
You see what I mean?

17:39.016 --> 17:42.268
Now, you get that trunk down
out of there. I'll get the satchel.

17:48.776 --> 17:50.943
Jackson, what's happening?

17:54.865 --> 17:57.450
Your old man's
got some roughshod ways.

17:57.534 --> 17:59.702
He's rubbed people
the wrong way around here.

17:59.787 --> 18:02.330
But he's a sweet old bear.
He wouldn't hurt anybody.

18:02.414 --> 18:04.457
Why, don't you think I know that?

18:04.541 --> 18:06.918
Nobody in this whole county
would give me a job,

18:07.002 --> 18:10.671
as though I was responsible for what
my people done to General Custer.

18:10.756 --> 18:13.424
I swear, I was a little baby at the time.

18:13.509 --> 18:18.721
But your daddy, well,
he gave me a job right off.

18:18.806 --> 18:20.932
Full wages too.

18:21.016 --> 18:25.353
I guess I respect and admire him
more'n I ever done anybody.

18:25.437 --> 18:28.147
This used to be the best
spread in the whole valley.

18:28.232 --> 18:30.608
Well, the town's got
a big outfit movin' in-

18:30.692 --> 18:32.777
build factories,

18:32.861 --> 18:35.321
make a real city of Wolf City.

18:35.405 --> 18:38.783
They want your daddy's water rights.
He won't sell, and-

18:38.867 --> 18:42.286
I'm going to build us lunch
as soon as we get this trunk inside.

18:42.371 --> 18:44.455
Papa, I'm gonna do
the cooking now.

18:44.540 --> 18:46.457
I'm gonna take care of you.

18:48.710 --> 18:51.587
[ Screams ]

18:56.218 --> 18:58.136
Frankie Ballou?

18:59.721 --> 19:01.639
Beat it, you.

19:18.198 --> 19:21.659
I didn't mean to scream,
but he came out of nowhere.

19:21.743 --> 19:25.872
And that nose! Who is he, Papa?
Give me a hand, Jackson.

19:29.960 --> 19:32.712
Papa, who is he?
Tim Strawn, I'll betcha.

19:32.796 --> 19:35.047
When I say shalom alechem to you,
you don't know nothin'.

19:35.132 --> 19:38.009
Now suddenly, you're a mine of information!
Jackson, who is he?

19:38.093 --> 19:41.762
He's a murderer, a hired killer.
His nose was bit off in a fight.

19:41.847 --> 19:46.350
If I was gonna be scared, I'd be scared
of the fella who bit it off, not him.

19:46.435 --> 19:48.519
Papa- I can take care
of myself, Catherine.

19:48.604 --> 19:52.690
I always have and I always will. Don't let
it bother you none. It don't bother me.

19:52.774 --> 19:54.692
Papa, you've gotta do something about it.

19:54.776 --> 19:57.320
What we're gonna do, Catherine,
is go on livin'.

19:57.404 --> 20:00.031
We're gonna eat and we're gonna
sleep and we're gonna work.

20:00.115 --> 20:04.952
And tomorrow, we're gonna go
celebrate the Fall Harvest Day.

20:05.954 --> 20:07.872
Take care of the horses, Jackson.

20:21.136 --> 20:24.138
Mabel.
[ Chuckles ]

20:38.987 --> 20:40.905
[ Grunts ]

20:40.989 --> 20:44.033
Hey.
Well.

20:44.117 --> 20:48.079
Now, there's a game for a sheriff-
liar's poker.

20:48.163 --> 20:51.040
[ Laughing ] We got
our unemployed off the streets...

20:51.124 --> 20:54.293
and made Wolf City safe
all in one brilliant stroke.

20:54.378 --> 20:56.420
They grabbed Ed Cardigan for sheriff.

20:56.505 --> 20:58.923
Oh, he's good.
He's too lazy to steal and too dumb to-

20:59.007 --> 21:02.093
Ballou! I'll ask you to show
a little respect for these ladies-

21:02.177 --> 21:05.388
Take off your hat.
You're meetin' my daughter, Catherine.

21:05.472 --> 21:08.266
Well, I'll be damned.
If it ain't little-

21:08.350 --> 21:10.768
Cardigan, you can talk to me
any way you please.

21:10.852 --> 21:13.187
You're talkin' to my daughter,
so watch your damn language!

21:14.773 --> 21:17.775
Nice to see you back in Wolf City,
Miss Ballou.

21:17.859 --> 21:22.154
You got any idea who forked about
a ton of manure down my well?

21:22.239 --> 21:24.198
Well, no.

21:24.283 --> 21:26.450
[ Mocking Sheriff ] Well, no.

21:26.535 --> 21:28.786
Some sheriff.

21:28.870 --> 21:30.788
Come on, Catherine.

21:32.124 --> 21:34.083
Are you really a sheriff?

21:34.167 --> 21:36.127
Why is it hard to believe?

21:36.211 --> 21:38.838
Well, why don't you help him?

21:38.922 --> 21:41.705
I think someone's poisoned that
water to drive him off his ranch.

21:41.730 --> 21:42.657
That's what I think.

21:42.718 --> 21:44.885
Yesterday, a man named Strawn
came to the house-

21:44.970 --> 21:47.805
Miss Catherine, there are
certain ramifications...

21:47.889 --> 21:50.141
to peace officerin' that
you wouldn't understand.

21:50.225 --> 21:53.394
Now, please, believe me.
I'm taking care of it my way.

21:53.478 --> 21:55.563
What ramifications?

21:55.647 --> 21:58.482
Don't you worry your pretty
little head about it.

21:58.567 --> 22:00.484
You go ahead
and have a good time.

22:00.569 --> 22:02.153
Oh!

22:06.199 --> 22:08.326
♪♪ [ Continues ]

22:08.410 --> 22:10.411
Jackson, am I mad.

22:10.495 --> 22:13.998
I know.
I saw you talkin' to Sheriff Cardigan.

22:14.082 --> 22:16.542
Ooh, he's-
[ Sighs ] just like Papa.

22:16.626 --> 22:19.712
He pats me on the head
and tells me to run along.

22:19.796 --> 22:22.423
What am I gonna do?

22:22.507 --> 22:24.800
They got a gunfighter.

22:24.885 --> 22:26.802
You get a gunfighter.

22:31.433 --> 22:35.728
Jackson, there's a funny,
inscrutable look on your face.

22:35.812 --> 22:38.522
I can't tell if you're
making fun of me or not.

22:38.607 --> 22:43.361
Wouldn't nobody bother your daddy with old
Wild Bill Hickok or Bat Masterson around.

22:43.445 --> 22:47.073
- [ Applause ]
- Come on, Jackson.

22:47.157 --> 22:50.743
♪♪ [ Man Singing, Indistinct ]
Come on.

22:50.827 --> 22:54.872
♪ Forward up and back you go
Forward again with a do Si do ♪

22:54.956 --> 22:56.957
♪ All join hands and form a ring ♪

22:57.042 --> 22:59.543
♪ And circle to the left
with the dear little thing ♪

23:00.879 --> 23:03.089
♪♪ [ Continues ]
Who could I get?

23:03.173 --> 23:05.383
Kid Shelleen.
There really is a Kid Shelleen?

23:05.467 --> 23:07.738
I thought he was just in books.
He's real.

23:07.763 --> 23:10.245
One of the best of 'em
to my way of thinkin'.

23:10.305 --> 23:14.141
Well, what can I do? You can write
him a letter. I'll mail it.

23:20.732 --> 23:23.484
No call to dance with Jackson?
No call not to.

23:23.568 --> 23:25.861
He's an Injun.

23:30.867 --> 23:33.285
Scream! [ Laughs ]

23:35.831 --> 23:38.249
I like Jackson.
You're gonna make trouble for him.

23:38.333 --> 23:40.167
Oh, look who's talking about trouble.

23:40.252 --> 23:41.919
♪ Hand over hand
Go around the ring ♪

23:42.003 --> 23:44.713
♪ When you meet your partner,
give her a swing ♪

23:49.261 --> 23:51.137
What are you doing here?
Looking for you.

23:51.221 --> 23:53.639
You're an outlaw! Sure am.
Got a price on my head.

23:53.723 --> 23:57.852
Shh! Twenty-five dollars for
Jed, thirty-five dollars for me.

24:06.528 --> 24:08.946
[ All Whooping ]

24:16.037 --> 24:19.707
I wanna thank you, ma'am,
for all your help to my nephew and I.

24:30.343 --> 24:34.805
Where are you staying? On the run,
ma'am, hidin' out in the crowd.

24:34.890 --> 24:36.932
Won't inflict myself on you any further.

24:37.017 --> 24:38.737
♪ Swing and whirl
your pretty little thing ♪

24:38.768 --> 24:41.145
♪ Then face your partner
and leave the ring ♪

24:54.576 --> 24:56.827
Have you got a gun?
Sure do.

24:56.912 --> 24:59.538
Come home with me tonight.
Say, "Please."

24:59.623 --> 25:01.582
Please!

25:15.639 --> 25:18.057
♪ Circle eight
and go around the town ♪

25:25.148 --> 25:27.191
♪ Swing your gal
if she ain't too tall ♪

25:27.275 --> 25:29.193
♪ With her head in the kitchen
and her feet in the hall ♪

25:29.277 --> 25:31.195
♪ Watch your partner
Watch her grin ♪

25:31.279 --> 25:33.197
♪ Muss up her hair
and kick her in the shins ♪

25:37.202 --> 25:39.119
You dance so well.

25:39.204 --> 25:41.455
Simple, like some we learn
on the reservation.

25:41.540 --> 25:46.252
Buffalo dance, rain dance, war dance.

25:46.336 --> 25:48.837
Is the square dance anything
like a war dance?

25:48.922 --> 25:50.839
This one is.

26:00.976 --> 26:04.228
I wanna talk to you, Lo.
My name isn't Lo.

26:06.565 --> 26:10.234
Wait a minute. Isn't it?

26:10.318 --> 26:12.903
I thought it was Lo-

26:12.988 --> 26:15.614
the poor Indian.

26:18.868 --> 26:22.538
Well, it's Custer's Last Stand all over,
with me in the middle.

26:22.622 --> 26:24.498
[ Woman Screaming ]

26:32.007 --> 26:33.882
Hey!

26:33.967 --> 26:35.926
Come on, you! Jackson, you all right?

26:40.765 --> 26:42.766
Shalom alechem!

26:42.851 --> 26:45.269
♪♪ [ Tempo Increases ]

27:01.036 --> 27:03.912
[ Whooping ]

27:13.381 --> 27:15.549
[ Whooping ]

27:39.199 --> 27:40.616
Atta girl, Mabel!

27:42.327 --> 27:44.119
One, two, and a right!

27:46.414 --> 27:47.998
And a right!

27:52.170 --> 27:56.757
Mabel, my six-foot dove.

28:03.640 --> 28:06.058
♪♪ [ Fades ]

28:08.395 --> 28:10.312
♪ O' wines and beers ♪

28:10.397 --> 28:14.650
♪ The goat and sheep
die at 29 ♪

28:14.734 --> 28:19.196
♪ And never taste
o' scotch and rye ♪

28:19.280 --> 28:24.410
♪ Yet some of them a very few ♪

28:24.494 --> 28:29.832
♪ Stay pickled till they're 92 ♪

28:29.916 --> 28:35.295
♪ Yeah, some of them a very few ♪

28:35.380 --> 28:41.427
♪ Stay pickled till they're 92 ♪♪

28:44.973 --> 28:47.391
My little schoolteacher.

28:47.475 --> 28:49.810
I guess we showed 'em, eh, kitten?

28:49.894 --> 28:52.312
I got north, you take south.
Yeah.

28:52.397 --> 28:54.314
Up!

28:57.944 --> 28:59.862
[ Laughs ]

29:02.323 --> 29:04.825
Where to? Straight
ahead, on the sofa.

29:06.828 --> 29:08.871
Oh.

29:08.955 --> 29:11.915
Do you think that pair of freeloaders
is gonna stop Strawn?

29:12.000 --> 29:15.919
Well, they're gunmen, Jackson. They got
a price on their head. They told me.

29:17.505 --> 29:20.883
What a fine place, ma'am.

29:20.967 --> 29:22.885
Nice living room.

29:24.053 --> 29:26.013
Kitchen.

29:26.097 --> 29:29.266
Back of the house.

29:29.350 --> 29:31.268
Bedroom.

29:31.352 --> 29:33.562
You sleep in the barn.

29:34.731 --> 29:37.983
Thank you, ma'am.
Always deeper in your debt.

29:41.404 --> 29:45.032
Oh, what a good time I had today.
[ Door Closes ]

29:56.544 --> 29:58.462
[ Makes Kissing Sound ]

30:04.219 --> 30:06.178
♪♪ [ Humming ]

30:11.226 --> 30:13.143
[ Sighs ]

30:26.449 --> 30:28.367
[ Gasps ]

30:28.451 --> 30:31.495
[ Makes Kissing Sound ]
Hey, you always pucker before retirin'?

30:31.579 --> 30:33.997
Get out of here!
How did you get in here?

30:34.082 --> 30:36.041
Get out!
Why?

30:36.125 --> 30:38.919
If my father knew you were here,
he'd kill you.

30:39.003 --> 30:42.256
Oh, you couldn't wake your father
with a 21 -gun salute.

30:42.340 --> 30:44.424
[ Gasps ] Come on in
and we'll play spoon!

30:44.509 --> 30:47.553
You are absolutely
the most... [ Yells ]

30:52.600 --> 30:55.269
Well, I guess I figured wrong.

30:58.773 --> 31:00.315
Where are you going?

31:02.610 --> 31:06.029
Back to the barn. Your father's horse
snores, but I've slept through worse.

31:06.114 --> 31:07.489
Oh, no, don't go.

31:10.118 --> 31:12.995
No. Say, I gotta talk to you.

31:14.831 --> 31:15.831
Okay.

31:19.460 --> 31:22.170
We'll talk first.

31:22.255 --> 31:25.507
Well, I-I can't talk with you sittin'
right there on the bed like that.

31:25.592 --> 31:27.384
Try.

31:29.262 --> 31:32.347
Clay, my father's a wonderful man.
I wonder if you realize that.

31:32.432 --> 31:35.893
- Oh, sure do.
- Well, they hate him.

31:35.977 --> 31:39.062
They're trying to drive him off this ranch.
They've put manure in his well,

31:39.147 --> 31:41.064
they've made him talk to lawyers,

31:41.149 --> 31:43.358
and they've sent a gunman
to drive him off.

31:43.443 --> 31:47.237
- You're dreamin'.
- No, he's real! I saw him.

31:47.322 --> 31:49.489
I'll help you pack.

31:49.574 --> 31:54.077
I suppose to a man like you
a little farm like this is just dirt.

31:54.162 --> 31:56.079
To him it's his whole life!

31:56.164 --> 31:58.540
Let him fight like a man.
I'll help you pack.

32:00.168 --> 32:02.419
You are absolutely useless.

32:02.503 --> 32:05.172
[ Chuckles ] You are absolutely right.

32:05.256 --> 32:07.633
Oh!

32:10.136 --> 32:14.598
Look, why don't you hire yourself
a gunfighter? I mean, they got one.

32:14.682 --> 32:16.683
[ Sobbing ]

32:18.770 --> 32:20.687
Uh-

32:25.735 --> 32:28.570
You always make that little...
[ Makes Kissing Sound ] in the mirror?

32:28.655 --> 32:30.572
Oh, no.

32:41.751 --> 32:46.046
- Where are you going?
- The barn.

32:46.130 --> 32:47.714
Don't go.

32:49.342 --> 32:50.592
What now?

32:51.594 --> 32:54.554
Clay, I just don't believe it
when you say you're-

32:54.639 --> 32:56.974
you're useless and cynical like that.

32:57.058 --> 32:59.393
I mean, everybody
has to have some good in him...

32:59.477 --> 33:03.772
no matter how depraved
and cowardly he thinks he is.

33:03.856 --> 33:07.985
You know, you are a sugar plum,

33:08.069 --> 33:10.320
and you'd better watch out,

33:10.405 --> 33:12.531
because there are a lot of people...

33:12.615 --> 33:16.243
that are just as depraved and cowardly
as they think they are.

33:16.327 --> 33:19.287
And one of 'em one of these days...

33:19.372 --> 33:22.499
is gonna eat you right up.

33:23.710 --> 33:25.669
Evening, ma'am.
Air and moonlight...

33:25.753 --> 33:28.088
sets the bull to talkin'
to each other for sure.

33:28.172 --> 33:32.050
What do you want, Uncle? Well, I was just
wonderin' if we was stayin' the night.

33:32.135 --> 33:35.012
I'd, uh, take off my boots
before goin' to sleep.

33:35.096 --> 33:38.807
Jed, I helped you on the train. Will you
help me now? Certainly, ma'am. Anything.

33:38.891 --> 33:42.686
Stay here with us.
There's somebody trying to kill my father.

33:42.770 --> 33:44.646
No!
Jed-

33:44.731 --> 33:46.690
- Oh, Jed.
- We'll stay, ma'am.

33:46.774 --> 33:50.610
- Be our pleasure to do what we can.
- We don't need him then.

33:50.695 --> 33:52.696
Oh, I think you do.

33:52.780 --> 33:56.700
And my uncle here ain't never shot
at a man. It's against his principles.

33:56.784 --> 33:57.775
Is that true?

33:57.800 --> 34:00.770
Oh, yes, ma'am, that's true.
But neither has he.

34:02.040 --> 34:05.709
But we'll stay and do what we can.
Yeah.

34:06.961 --> 34:10.297
[ Sighs ] As long as
there ain't no trouble.

34:59.263 --> 35:01.556
♪ Then there came to town ♪

35:01.641 --> 35:03.725
♪ A gun deadly and frightenin' ♪

35:03.810 --> 35:05.936
♪ A gun quicker than lightenin' ♪

35:06.020 --> 35:09.314
♪ Fastest gun you've seen ♪

35:09.398 --> 35:12.192
♪ It was the gun
in the hand of ♪

35:12.276 --> 35:16.530
♪ Steel-eyed Kid Shelleen ♪

35:38.886 --> 35:41.138
♪ Just one look at him ♪

35:41.222 --> 35:43.265
♪ Had folks startin' to booger ♪

35:43.349 --> 35:48.645
♪ Wild, wild as a cougar
Proud and fierce and mean ♪

35:48.729 --> 35:52.315
♪ There was no man
who was tougher ♪

35:52.400 --> 35:56.278
♪ Tough as Kid Shelleen ♪

36:12.003 --> 36:17.591
♪ He had the eyes of a killer ♪
♪ Cold as the devil ♪

36:17.675 --> 36:21.887
♪ The look of a killer ♪
♪ The look of a devil ♪

36:21.971 --> 36:25.974
♪ The face of a killer ♪
♪ That man was the devil ♪

36:26.058 --> 36:29.853
♪ Just wild and ornery
and mean ♪

36:29.937 --> 36:32.063
♪ Kid Shelleen ♪

36:32.148 --> 36:34.316
♪ Kid Shelleen ♪

36:34.400 --> 36:37.861
♪ The fastest gun you've ever seen ♪♪

36:42.992 --> 36:44.951
Kid Shelleen.

36:47.747 --> 36:50.540
Come on. You've had
a couple of hours to sleep it off.

36:50.625 --> 36:53.543
Let me see what my daughter
laid out 50 bucks for.

37:04.305 --> 37:06.348
Well? What's holdin' you up?

37:06.432 --> 37:09.517
No gun.
All right, go get it!

37:09.602 --> 37:12.229
I hocked it, I think. St. Louis?

37:12.313 --> 37:14.272
[ Papa ] Geez!

37:14.357 --> 37:17.067
You mean you drank up
the whole 50 bucks she sent ya?

37:17.151 --> 37:19.736
Fifty bucks!

37:19.820 --> 37:22.572
Now look what you did to him!
You could have killed him...

37:22.657 --> 37:25.659
giving him 50 bucks worth
of whiskey all at once!

37:25.743 --> 37:26.723
Fifty bucks!

37:26.748 --> 37:29.687
Papa, how was I supposed
to know he was a drunk?

37:44.679 --> 37:46.388
Go on and shoot, Kid.

37:46.472 --> 37:48.598
Bang away, old fella.

38:03.489 --> 38:08.034
You'd like a drink better'n a poke in
the eye with a sharp stob, wouldn't you?

38:16.627 --> 38:18.795
He did it! He missed the barn!

38:22.883 --> 38:27.304
Sir, if I could just have one little
nip to steady my hands. [ Groans ]

38:27.388 --> 38:30.598
I had the typhoid real bad.
I had a rough trip down here.

38:30.683 --> 38:32.851
If I could just...
I didn't get no sleep.

38:32.935 --> 38:36.521
If I could have one little nip,
you know. Please.

38:42.361 --> 38:43.945
Jackson?
Yeah?

38:44.030 --> 38:48.033
You got that bottle you always carry
to make that sheriff mad?

38:48.117 --> 38:50.076
Give him some.

39:03.299 --> 39:06.426
[ Exhales, Coughs ]

39:08.804 --> 39:11.348
You're an Injun, ain't ya?
Yeah.

39:11.432 --> 39:13.683
That's all right.
I ain't got nothin' against Injuns.

39:13.768 --> 39:16.686
Yeah, they was a breed of men
in the old West.

39:16.771 --> 39:20.315
But it's all over for them
just like it is for the gunfighter,

39:20.399 --> 39:24.361
except they didn't give us no reservation
or teach us how to weave rugs.

39:28.449 --> 39:30.408
See you later, son.

39:32.370 --> 39:34.287
Yeah.

39:36.916 --> 39:39.125
[ Exhales Deeply ]

39:45.633 --> 39:47.634
Yeah, it's all over in Dodge.

39:47.718 --> 39:50.261
Tombstone too.
Cheyenne, Deadwood, all gone.

39:50.346 --> 39:52.931
All dead and gone.

39:53.015 --> 39:55.266
Pow!

40:00.856 --> 40:03.108
Why, the last time
I come through Tombstone,

40:03.192 --> 40:05.652
the big excitement there
was about the new roller skating rink...

40:05.736 --> 40:07.779
that they'd laid out over the OK Corral.

40:07.863 --> 40:09.781
I'll tell you something else.
I used to work...

40:09.865 --> 40:12.575
the Buffalo Bill Wild West Show
at the Congress of Rough Riders,

40:12.660 --> 40:14.619
and I rescued many
a stagecoach passenger...

40:14.703 --> 40:17.914
from road agents and drunken Injuns
in the nick of time.

40:17.998 --> 40:20.208
Twice a day,
three times on Saturday.

40:35.850 --> 40:37.851
[ Yells ]

40:42.314 --> 40:44.482
Where did it go?

40:50.156 --> 40:52.282
You see a man with his eyes set...

40:52.366 --> 40:55.618
and his head on the bias like,
his teeth anchored like a mule-

40:55.703 --> 41:00.373
Well, he'd just as soon hang your guts on a
fence post as say, "Great day in the mornin'."

41:00.458 --> 41:04.252
Well, he a gunfighter,
proud and feared o' nothin'.

41:04.336 --> 41:07.630
'Cause ain't nothin' walk on this earth
he got to bow down to.

41:07.715 --> 41:11.342
Not a man don't tip his hat,
not a boy don't know his name,

41:11.427 --> 41:13.553
and ain't no place he ain't welcome,

41:13.637 --> 41:15.555
because when a gunfighter around,

41:15.639 --> 41:17.849
trouble just naturally stay away, huh?

41:17.933 --> 41:21.978
Folks sayin',
"Hiya, Kid. How you doin', Kid?

41:22.062 --> 41:25.523
Come on in and have a pitcher of milk
and some gingerbread.

41:25.608 --> 41:29.319
Or come up on the porch and cool
your heels for a while. It's hot outside."

41:29.403 --> 41:33.990
Because nobody don't make
no fun of a friend of Kid Shelleen.

41:34.074 --> 41:37.076
Miss Ballou, I am here!

41:38.704 --> 41:41.623
I never seen a man
get through a day so fast.

41:41.707 --> 41:43.583
You leave him alone.

41:43.667 --> 41:46.878
Cat, I ain't runnin' no dude ranch
for misfits and unemployables.

41:46.962 --> 41:48.963
Now, you keep him away from me.

41:51.717 --> 41:53.885
Where are you gonna go now, Kid?

41:53.969 --> 41:57.013
Why, Miss Ballou,
you paid me 50 dollars.

41:57.097 --> 42:00.350
I aim to stay and earn it.

42:04.146 --> 42:06.981
He can sleep in the barn, Jackson.

42:08.609 --> 42:10.735
It's my gun.
Hmm?

42:10.819 --> 42:12.779
Oh.

42:17.076 --> 42:20.578
Say, uh, Mr. Shelleen?
Hmm?

42:20.663 --> 42:22.622
Okay if I carry your valise?

42:22.706 --> 42:25.166
Why, sure, kid.

42:25.251 --> 42:27.460
Oh, I ain't got no cash.

42:27.545 --> 42:31.381
Oh, no need to tip me, sir. It's gonna
be a pleasure to see you at work.

42:31.465 --> 42:34.551
[ Sighs ]

42:34.635 --> 42:37.762
Uh, how many in the opposition?

42:37.846 --> 42:39.973
Oh, just one- Tim Strawn.

42:46.105 --> 42:49.524
Well, waste not, want not.
Where's that jug of yours?

43:04.415 --> 43:07.333
Strawn. Are you sure?

43:07.418 --> 43:09.711
Yep, silver nose and all.

43:21.432 --> 43:23.349
Let Shelleen do it.

43:23.434 --> 43:26.603
Shelleen isn't in any condition
to be- He sure isn't.

43:26.687 --> 43:29.606
Look, I'm counting on you,
all three of you.

43:29.690 --> 43:33.067
My papa's a stubborn mule, and he's
gonna take chances, and I can't let him.

43:33.152 --> 43:35.112
You gotta stick with him.
[ Together ] Yes, ma'am.

43:35.195 --> 43:37.614
[ Papa ] All right. Everywhere
he goes, no matter where.

43:37.698 --> 43:40.867
You unemployables. Now,
let's get the day's work done.

43:42.494 --> 43:45.955
Oh, for the love of Mike.
A drunk in the bunkhouse...

43:46.040 --> 43:48.249
and a circus act following me around!

43:48.334 --> 43:50.251
Don't let him out of your sight.

43:50.336 --> 43:53.129
Shelleen don't have tobacco,
does he? Could set fire to the barn.

43:53.213 --> 43:55.506
No, he's sleepin' it off, poor soul.

43:57.509 --> 43:59.427
Do you mind?

44:01.013 --> 44:03.389
For cryin' up a storm!
What do you boys think you're doin'?

44:03.474 --> 44:07.477
Cat said stick with you, and stick it is.
She's crazy, I tell ya.

44:07.561 --> 44:09.979
Always has been.

44:10.064 --> 44:13.316
She sees things.
Her mother was like that.

44:13.400 --> 44:16.235
In the middle of the night,
she seen moon men...

44:16.320 --> 44:19.822
creepin' down the walls.

44:19.907 --> 44:24.202
Now, get away! I could trip on one of
you and get trampled in the crowd.

44:24.286 --> 44:26.537
Why was I cursed in my old age...

44:26.622 --> 44:29.999
with a nutty daughter and
a bunch of slack-twisted idiots?

44:30.084 --> 44:33.127
Who's here to threaten me?
You see anyone over there?

44:33.212 --> 44:35.505
Or there?

44:35.589 --> 44:38.091
Or over that way? Huh?

44:38.175 --> 44:40.593
Do you see anybody anywhere?

44:40.678 --> 44:44.430
Now, stand back and let me breathe!

44:46.475 --> 44:49.227
[ Gunshot ]

44:53.190 --> 44:56.818
Drop the gun belts.

45:02.157 --> 45:04.117
No!

45:15.629 --> 45:17.547
No!

45:42.656 --> 45:44.323
Whoa!

45:57.171 --> 45:59.964
You're a murderer!

46:00.048 --> 46:02.759
You're gonna hang! What is it?
What's wrong?

46:02.843 --> 46:04.927
You killed my father!

46:05.012 --> 46:07.513
That can't be. He's been sittin'
right there all mornin'.

46:07.598 --> 46:08.515
No, I saw him.

46:08.540 --> 46:11.291
He hasn't been out of that
rocker all mornin' long.

46:11.351 --> 46:14.771
- It's a fact.
- Why do you say that?

46:14.855 --> 46:17.982
Just telling the truth.

46:26.867 --> 46:30.411
So that's the way it's gonna be?
Better get out of here.

46:30.496 --> 46:32.121
No! No!

46:32.206 --> 46:35.917
Wait a minute. Get her off of here.
Get her out of here!

46:36.001 --> 46:38.461
[ Grunting ] Cat! Don't you do that!
Don't you-

46:38.545 --> 46:41.088
- [ Gunshot ]
- Put that gun away!

46:41.173 --> 46:43.841
Get that gun away from her!

46:46.970 --> 46:49.388
You stop it!

46:53.060 --> 46:55.478
You won't make me cry.

47:00.359 --> 47:02.318
You'll never make me cry.

47:02.402 --> 47:09.116
♪ There are teardrops
in her heart ♪

47:09.201 --> 47:14.831
♪ But they can't make her cry ♪

